Contributing Guidelines
                           Version 1.0, June 2026
                           https://spacescale.io

   GUIDELINES FOR CONTRIBUTING TO THIS PROJECT

   1. Issues.

      Each issue must be self contained and describe exactly one thing.
      Before creating a new issue, search existing issues to confirm it
      has not already been reported or proposed.

   2. Pull Requests.

      Keep pull requests small and focused on one change. Reference the
      issue number in the pull request description. All pull requests
      must target the dev branch unless explicitly stated otherwise.

   3. Tests.

      New features must include tests that verify the intended behavior.
      Bug fixes should include a test that reproduces the original failure
      when practical.

   4. Code Style.

      Follow the existing conventions in the codebase. Run the project
      linter and formatter before submitting. Do not introduce unrelated
      formatting changes in the same pull request.

   5. AI Disclosure.

      If any portion of a contribution was generated or substantially
      assisted by AI tooling, this must be disclosed in the pull request
      description.

   6. Commit Messages.

      Write concise commit messages that describe what changed and why.
      Use the imperative mood. Prefix with a type when appropriate:
      feat, fix, docs, ci, chore.

   END OF GUIDELINES
